bio.openEndedText:
Hello there, I'm Nikita. I am from Moldova, but have lived in Arizona for the last two decades. My professional background is in the legal field, but I'm also a car enthusiast, and I have a specific interest in electric cars. 

Each vehicle in my fleet isn't just a rental; it's a personal choice- a car I'd happily take for a spin myself. I've learned to take care of everything in my life, and that philosophy extends to my four-wheeled companions.

From zippy electric rides to robust gas guzzlers, my fleet covers all the bases. Whether you're panning a weekend escape, a family road trip, or just need a reliable ride for errands, I've got you covered.

Now, let's talk honesty, cleanliness, and punctuality. These aren't just virtues to me; they're the backbone of my approach. I believe in being upfront about my cars and delivering on time, and I appreciate it when my guests reciprocate with respect for the vehicles I provide.

In a nutshell, I'm not just a Turo host – I'm a guy who loves what he does, takes pride in his cars, and wants you to experience the same joy and reliability that I get from them. So, if you're in Arizona and need a set of wheels, hit me up. I've got the keys to your next great drive!

Here is my small fleet of 10 cars (you can also find them by scrolling through my profile):


2017 Chevrolet Bolt (Fully electric - 263 miles of range)
2022 Tesla Model 3 (Fully Electric - 260 miles of range)
2022 Tesla Model Y (7 seats and - 320 miles of range)
2017 VW Tiguan (AWD & 7 seats - regular Gas vehicle)
2017 Chrysler Pacifica (8 seats - comfortable, family)
2016 & 2017 Fiat 500e (limited range electric Car for short distances).

I am originally from a small town in southern Iowa called Osceola where my wife is from Huron, South Dakota.  My wife and I met while both attending pharmacy school at South Dakota State University.  After graduation, we both moved to greater metropolitan Phoenix to begin our pharmacy careers with Walgreens in 2006.  We are both currently employed at Strive Compounding Pharmacy and have many outside interests that keep our family busy.  We both grew up with fathers who were small business owners and mothers who encouraged us to follow our dreams!  Therefore in 2009, we bought our first "house to flip".  We've had a blast flipping houses with many great learning lessons.  Over the years, the outside interests crescendoed into Turo!  I've personally always loved a wide variety of cars.  Turo has given us the opportunity to explore the hobby and offer our favorites back to the ride sharing community.  We work hard to provide a fabulous car coupled with exceptional service.  As you can see, we've strived to maintain a great track record of satisfied clientele!

Hello, my name is Johnny Vo and I am an aspiring physical therapy student aiming to pay off my Doctorate's in Physical Therapy by myself!
I am 26 years old and my birthday is October 26, 1995. A Scorpio 🦂! Take that knowledge as you will. I just recently finished my bachelor’s at Arizona State University as of 2022! Woot Woot 🙌

I graduated a little late compared to a lot of other people my age but that’s a long story related to some family shabam I will not bore you with unless you want to be bored with. I was actually born in Sacramento California but our family moved here to Arizona back in 2002 and we have been here since! I love the desert and all of it’s brown dusty beauty. The sunsets here are one of a kind and the drives through the mountains are inviting and relaxing. 

I have traveled to many places likes Montana, Idaho, Oregon, Nevada, and even outside the United States to Vietnam! I’m fluent in Vietnamese since I was raised bilingual. I do know a small amount of Spanish as well in case someone needs assistance. 

My hobbies are not as excited as many other people. I dabbled in a little bit of anything because I get pretty bored fast; however, I am a long term practitioner for mixed martial arts specializing in Muay Thai for health and conditioning but nothing too fancy. So if you like fighting, we can totally talk about that! I love being active as since I am very into the human body and the kinesiology behind it. Everything from how the body moves and how it should move biomechanically for each individual is absolutely striking to me. 

This leads me to why I have decided to pop onto Turo as not only a way to get connected with the car lovers of the world, but to learn more on how to properly make extra income on the side in order to pay for my upcoming Doctorate’s of Physical Therapy program. I’m not sure if y’all knew this, apparently a Doctorate program is not cheap regardless of what field you decide to take🥴. I know going on a car app is such an oddball and random approach compared to everything I have been involved in but hey, it sounds like fun. And in the end, isn’t that what we’re all on this app to do? Rent a car for a fun trip somewhere? Or rent a car for a fun leisurely ride for the weekend? Or a fun ride to… work? Regardless of the factor, I think this is a cool app to play with and I’m all for it. I can even rent my dream car on here which is a Maserati for a weekend 👀 It’s kind of cool being able to just rent and test drive all sorts of different cars. I think this will be a fun experience for both me and you! 

If you want to stay connected with me and get to know me better as a person, I do have a Facebook and Instagram that I hardly use! Feel free to add me on both and don’t be a stranger! 
I go by Asianinboots on Instagram! Long story, but it’s a fun one! I’m full of stories.
